Grid War Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 05/17/2023

Thank you for choosing to play Grid War!
This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose information about players of the Game ("you" or "user"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. By using the Grid War, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information: When you play the Grid War, we may collect certain personal information that can identify you directly or indirectly, such as your name, email address, and device identifiers. We only collect personal information that is necessary for providing and improving the Game.
1.2 Usage Data: We may collect non-personal information about how you interact with and use the Game. This may include information about your device, in-game activities, gameplay preferences, and other statistical data. This information is used for analyzing and enhancing the Game's performance and user experience.

How We Use Your Information
2.1 Personal Information: We may use your personal information to:
a) Provide and improve the Game's functionality and features.
b) Respond to your inquiries and fulfill your requests.
c) Send you important updates, announcements, and administrative information related to the Game.
d) Personalize your experience and offer tailored content and recommendations.
e) Communicate with you regarding customer support and technical issues.
f) Protect against fraud, unauthorized activities, and potential violations of our terms of service.
g) Comply with legal obligations and enforce our rights.

2.2 Usage Data: We may use non-personal information, including usage data, for various purposes, such as:

a) Analyzing trends and patterns to improve the Game's performance.
b) Monitoring and optimizing the Game's functionality.
c) Enhancing user experience by offering personalized content.
d) Conducting research, analytics, and other internal purposes.

Information Sharing and Disclosure
3.1 Third-Party Service Providers: We may engage third-party service providers to perform certain functions on our behalf, such as hosting, data analysis, customer support, and marketing assistance. These providers may have access to your personal information only to the extent necessary to perform their tasks and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.
3.2 Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or government agency).

3.3 Business Transfers: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, we may transfer your personal information to the acquiring entity as part of the transaction. We will notify you via email and/or a prominent notice on our website of any change in ownership or use of your personal information.

Data Security
We are committed to protecting the security of your personal information. We implement reasonable safeguards to prevent unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee absolute security.

Third-Party Services
The Game may integrate with third-party services, such as Firebase, for the storage and processing of user information. These third-party services have their own privacy policies, and we encourage you to review them. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these third-party services.

Children's Privacy
The Game is not intended for individuals under the age of 3. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will promptly delete such information from our database.
